> This Middle Eastern-style dish was inspired by sayadieh, a rice dish with roots in Lebanon and Syria. It starts with a bed of fluffy golden rice cooked with earthy turmeric and flavorful seafood stock. You'll serve seared spiced tilapia fillets over the rice along with a colorful jumble of lemony roasted carrots and red onion. Finish this beautiful plate with a shower of crunchy hazelnuts and a sprinkle of fresh parsley for a homestyle meal that may just become your new favorite.

== Rice ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} and half the @turmeric{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{20-30%seconds}.

Stir in @seafood stock concentrate{1}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Carrots & Onion ==

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into ¼-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and slice @red onion{1} into ¼-inch-thick wedges. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Roughly chop @hazelnuts{1/2%ounce}. Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Toss carrots and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon}, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4 servings), a squeeze of lemon juice, @salt{}, @pepper{}, and as much lemon zest as you like. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Tilapia ==

Meanwhile, pat @tilapia{11%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously all over with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, half the @cumin{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), @salt{generous}, and @pepper{generous}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add tilapia and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Lower heat to medium if fish starts to brown too quickly.

== To Serve ==

Divide rice and roasted veggies between plates or #shallow bowls{} in separate sections. Top rice with tilapia; sprinkle with hazelnuts and parsley. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Tilapia is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.